// =============================================================================
// core.math.frameworks.bounded_arithmetic — weak-stratum framework packages
// =============================================================================
//
// Six bounded-arithmetic systems shipped as separate framework
// packages, organised by their complexity-class correspondence:
//
//     ν^weak | System    | Complexity class | Reference theory
//     ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//        0   | V_0        | LOGSPACE         | Cook-Reckhow 1979
//        1   | V_1        | P                | Cook-Nguyen 2010
//        2   | S_2_1      | P                | Buss 1986
//        3   | V_NP       | NP               | Cook-Nguyen 2010
//        4   | V_PH       | Polynomial Hier  | Cook-Nguyen 2010
//      ω-1   | I_Delta_0  | full bounded     | Buss-Krajicek
//
// At the boundary `I_Delta_0 → full arithmetic` there is a discrete
// jump in ν^weak: rank ω-1 on the weak side becomes rank ω on the full
// side (per Theorem 137.T discrete-jump lemma). Verification at any
// of these strata is *strictly weaker* than full-arithmetic
// verification: the @verify(complexity_typed) strategy (deferred to
// VVA-8 V1) is sound exactly because no L_Abs-realisation crosses the
// boundary.
//
// Each system file declares the framework + its proof obligations as
// trusted-boundary axioms; downstream code uses
// `@framework(bounded_arithmetic_<system>, "<citation>")` to record the
// dependency. CLI `verum audit --framework-axioms` flags the
// complexity class.
// =============================================================================

public mount core.math.frameworks.bounded_arithmetic.v_0;
public mount core.math.frameworks.bounded_arithmetic.v_1;
public mount core.math.frameworks.bounded_arithmetic.s_2_1;
public mount core.math.frameworks.bounded_arithmetic.v_np;
public mount core.math.frameworks.bounded_arithmetic.v_ph;
public mount core.math.frameworks.bounded_arithmetic.i_delta_0;
